The number of coronavirus cases in South Africa has risen by 1 241, bringing the total to 728 836.  74 more related deaths have also been reported. “Thirty-five from Eastern Cape; six from the Free State; eight from Gauteng; six from KwaZulu-Natal; eight from Northern Cape; and eleven from Western Cape,” says the Department of Health in a statement. This brings the total number of COVID-19 related deaths to 19 539. “Of the 74 deaths reported today, 10 were reported to have occurred in the past 24-48 hours: four in Eastern Cape; one in the Free State; one in KwaZulu Natal; and four in Western Cape.” The recoveries now stand at 659 249 which translates to a recovery rate of 90%. As of today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is  728 836, the total number of deaths is 19539 and the total number of recoveries is 659 249. pic.twitter.com/WOdoDOQLA9 — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) November 3, 2020 